<html>
<head>
  <title>Naver OAuth2</title>
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js" integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh" crossorigin="anonymous">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/popper.js@1.16.0/dist/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-Q6E9RHvbIyZFJoft+2mJbHaEWldlvI9IOYy5n3zV9zzTtmI3UksdQRVvoxMfooAo" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-wfSDF2E50Y2D1uUdj0O3uMBJnjuUD4Ih7YwaYd1iqfktj0Uod8GCExl3Og8ifwB6" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1 style="color:green;">Welcome to Naver OAuth2</h1>
    <a class="btn btn-success" href="{{ .url }}">Login with Naver</a>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ul class="list-group">
      <li class="list-group-item">1. Login with Naver</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">2. Check Naver access token</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">3. Get my information from Naver with access token</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">4. Check the user by the email that Naver gives</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">5. Signup if the user doesn't exist</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">6. Signin to get access token from Cognito</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">7. Get my information from Cognito</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">8. Confirm authentication working with Naver and Cognito</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
